Former SARS Commissioner, Tom Moyane will be the one asking questions at the state capture inquiry on Monday. JOHANNESBURG - Former SARS Commissioner, Tom Moyane will be the one asking questions at the state capture inquiry on Monday. Moyane will cross-examine Public Enterprises Minister, Pravin Gordhan. READ: Moyane, Gordhan to face off at state capture inquiry But only for a limited time, according to Deputy Chief Justice, Raymond Zondo. The commission will also hear testimony from former Sars employee and partner at Bain, Athol Williams. Tom Moyane will get his chance to cross-examine Public Enterprises Minister Pravin Gordhan. Slindile Xaba reports. Courtesy #DStv403